    "28281588": {
      "title": "On \"bent\" functions",
      "abstract": "Abstract Let P ( x ) be a function from GF (2 n ) to GF (2). P ( x ) is called \u201cbent\u201d if all Fourier coefficients of (\u22121) P(x) are \u00b11. The polynomial degree of a bent function P ( x ) is studied, as are the properties of the Fourier transform of (\u22121) P(x) , and a connection with Hadamard matrices."
    }
  }
}